            <value>Please tell him the importance of a follow-up visit and advise him to visit a doctor or health facility for regular check-ups.
1. 1. Mental patients have to take medicine regularly. If you don't take it regularly, the disease will not be completely cured and can flare up again.
2. Do not stop taking medicine without a doctor's advice, even if symptoms disappear.
3. People who take medicine should be examined at health institutions at least twice a year
4. There may be common side effects like dry mouth, weight gain, headache, blurred vision etc. if you see such side effects, contact the hotline no.</value>
